main event: A strip of six frames of a pentagon-shaped object with a chain that the object disappeared into was photographed in Yucca Valley, California on October 25, 1958.
interesting points: The object was stationary and photographed for a total of about six seconds.
Triangulation indicates the object photographed was a reflection.
The Air Technical Intelligence Center (ATIC) had the film enlarged but could not identify the object due to lack of detail.
The ATIC could not determine the true speeds and altitudes of the object since the camera's running rate could not be established.
The ATIC concluded that no further analysis would be possible due to the limited data available.
sighted object: a pentagon-shaped object with a chain
photographs: yes, the report includes a strip of six frames
